6">Livestock</a></li></ul></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref41837"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Industry">Industry</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref41838"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Industry#ref41838">Power and irrigation</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref41839"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Trade">Trade</a><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41840"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Trade#ref41840">Internal trade</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41841"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Trade#ref41841">External trade</a></li></ul></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref41842"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation">Transportation</a><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41843"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation#ref41843">Roads</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41844"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation#ref41844">Railways</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41845"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation#ref41845">Maritime transport</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41846"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation#ref41846">Waterways</a></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h3"><li data-target="#ref41847"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Transportation#ref41847">Air transportation</a></li></ul></li></ul><ul class="list-unstyled" data-level="h2"><li data-target="#ref272278"><a class="w-100" href="/web/20230429174024/https://www.britannica.com/place/South-America/Cultural-life">Cultural life</a></li></ul></div></li></ul>
                    
                    
                
            </div>

            

            
            
                
